# Git ignore for an OpenGL C++ project (Windows / MinGW / Visual Studio / CMake)
# Adjust the sections below to keep third-party vendor sources (e.g. `lib/`, `include/`) if you intentionally commit them.

# --- Build output ---
/build/
/bin/
/out/
/dist/
cmake-build-*/

# --- Compiled files ---
*.exe
*.out
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
*.lib
*.a
*.o
*.obj
*.lo
*.slo

# --- Debug / profiling ---
*.pdb
*.ilk
*.idb
*.sdf
*.ipch
*.prof
*.gcno
*.gcda

# --- CMake files ---
CMakeFiles/
CMakeCache.txt
cmake_install.cmake
Makefile.cmake
Build/

# --- IDE / editor ---
.vs/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.VC.db
*.VC.opendb
*.vcxproj.user
*.vcxproj.filters

# JetBrains CLion
cmake-build-*/

# --- Temp / backup ---
*.log
*.tmp
*.temp
*~
.#*
*.swp
*.bak
*.orig

# --- OS files ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Packaging / installers ---
*.msi
*.7z
*.zip
*.tar.gz

# --- Other generated files ---
*.d
*.dep
*.o.d

# --- Optional: ignore prebuilt third-party libraries ---
# If you vendor prebuilt libs in `lib/` you may want to ignore them. Uncomment if needed:
# /lib/*.a
# /lib/*.lib
# /lib/*.dll

# --- Keep sources, headers and third-party sources by default ---
# Do NOT ignore `src/`, `include/`, or third-party source directories unless you know
# those are regenerated or intentionally omitted from the repo.

